1
00:00:25,900 --> 00:00:27,590
Please.

2
00:01:42,510 --> 00:01:45,510
Your results are in, Ms. Monou.

3
00:01:45,510 --> 00:01:48,420
According to our diagnosis,

4
00:01:48,420 --> 00:01:50,980
you are infertile.

5
00:01:52,540 --> 00:01:58,490
A natural pregnancy
will be near impossible for your body.

6
00:01:58,490 --> 00:02:01,100
Even if you undergo a corrective procedure,

7
00:02:01,100 --> 00:02:06,980
you would only be 10% more likely
to become pregnant.

8
00:02:09,170 --> 00:02:13,120
I'm... infertile?

9
00:02:13,120 --> 00:02:16,240
Ms. Monou.

10
00:02:16,240 --> 00:02:20,150
Though your chances are low,
they are not zero.

11
00:02:20,150 --> 00:02:23,260
I advise you to discuss solutions

12
00:02:23,260 --> 00:02:26,800
with your fiancé as soon as possible,

13
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:29,220
and come visit our clinic again.

14
00:02:30,140 --> 00:02:32,120
I'm...

15
00:02:33,130 --> 00:02:34,800
Infertile.

16
00:02:42,210 --> 00:02:43,840
I'm sorry.

17
00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:52,740
I wanted to stay with you forever, Sui.

18
00:02:54,300 --> 00:02:56,510
But when my parents saw your records...

19
00:02:56,510 --> 00:02:57,450
[Diagnosis]

20
00:02:57,450 --> 00:03:00,120
They told me the marriage was off.

21
00:03:04,280 --> 00:03:06,820
I want to marry you, Sui.

22
00:03:06,820 --> 00:03:09,450
I don't care about your status or family.

23
00:03:09,450 --> 00:03:12,820
Don't worry, I'll get my parents to understand.

24
00:03:12,820 --> 00:03:14,770
Satoshi...

25
00:03:16,130 --> 00:03:19,900
But to help put my parents at ease,

26
00:03:19,900 --> 00:03:22,710
could I ask you to get a check-up first?

27
00:03:28,690 --> 00:03:32,550
I couldn't do anything more for you, okay?

28
00:03:33,510 --> 00:03:37,620
I mean, infertile? After seven years together?

29
00:03:40,570 --> 00:03:42,720
Damn it!

30
00:03:53,750 --> 00:03:57,620
- Congratulations!
- You're next!

31
00:03:57,620 --> 00:03:59,940
I wanted the bouquet...

32
00:03:59,940 --> 00:04:02,270
Thank you.

33
00:04:06,290 --> 00:04:07,550
Here.

34
00:04:07,550 --> 00:04:09,750
Flowers for my dear older sister.

35
00:04:09,750 --> 00:04:11,550
- For me?
- Yup.

36
00:04:11,550 --> 00:04:13,480
A little happiness, from me to you.

37
00:04:13,480 --> 00:04:15,540
Next it's your turn, okay?

38
00:04:18,380 --> 00:04:20,170
Thanks.

39
00:04:24,210 --> 00:04:30,170
Sui, thank you for raising me
in place of our parents.

40
00:04:31,680 --> 00:04:33,450
Rin...

41
00:04:34,670 --> 00:04:39,120
I was surprised to hear
you broke up with your fiancé.

42
00:04:39,120 --> 00:04:41,440
But...

43
00:04:41,440 --> 00:04:45,530
I know you'll find someone better, and fast.

44
00:04:46,200 --> 00:04:48,040
I'll always be rooting for you.

45
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:49,900
Thanks.

46
00:04:53,440 --> 00:04:58,480
Let's make sure our kids
become best friends, okay?

47
00:05:06,900 --> 00:05:10,720
I'm going to inherit this company.

48
00:05:10,720 --> 00:05:14,920
Of course I had to break up
with someone infertile.

49
00:05:14,920 --> 00:05:18,300
What? Sui is infertile?

50
00:05:18,300 --> 00:05:20,370
No wonder you ended things

51
00:05:20,370 --> 00:05:24,070
with the girl you were crazy for.

52
00:05:24,070 --> 00:05:26,430
Guess it can't be helped if she's infertile.

53
00:05:26,430 --> 00:05:28,700
She wouldn't get you an heir.

54
00:05:28,700 --> 00:05:31,610
But you didn't have to fire her, did you?

55
00:05:31,610 --> 00:05:33,270
I didn't fire her.

56
00:05:33,270 --> 00:05:34,940
Mom said...

57
00:05:38,870 --> 00:05:40,360
I mean.

58
00:05:41,280 --> 00:05:43,890
My parents said she was better off elsewhere.

59
00:05:45,580 --> 00:05:48,100
Sui's probably awkward here anyway.

60
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:50,710
But hey, if she's infertile,

61
00:05:50,710 --> 00:05:55,270
doesn't that mean you two can do it raw?

62
00:05:55,270 --> 00:05:59,040
That's a big win!

63
00:06:08,490 --> 00:06:10,830
Sui.

64
00:06:13,800 --> 00:06:15,490
Honestly, Sui.

65
00:06:15,490 --> 00:06:20,060
Don't listen to their vile words.

66
00:06:20,060 --> 00:06:21,230
Takizawa...

67
00:06:21,230 --> 00:06:25,040
They're practically saying
you've failed as a woman.

68
00:06:25,040 --> 00:06:28,330
- What?
- Unforgivable.

69
00:06:30,530 --> 00:06:33,880
Failed, as a woman.

70
00:06:35,890 --> 00:06:37,620
Did you say something?

71
00:06:37,620 --> 00:06:40,400
No, not at all.

72
00:06:41,960 --> 00:06:45,140
I'm planning your farewell party,

73
00:06:45,140 --> 00:06:48,950
so look forward to it, okay?

74
00:06:48,950 --> 00:06:50,620
Thank you.

75
00:06:50,620 --> 00:06:52,910
Aw, this is nothing.

76
00:06:52,910 --> 00:06:55,850
Especially given how much you've done for me.

77
00:06:55,850 --> 00:06:59,820
I'll make sure we send you off with a blast.

78
00:06:59,820 --> 00:07:01,530
Thanks.

79
00:07:01,530 --> 00:07:06,280
Let's enjoy these last few days together!

80
00:07:19,630 --> 00:07:21,930
[Monou]

81
00:07:37,110 --> 00:07:40,640
To Rin's marriage,
and your graduation from parent status.

82
00:07:40,640 --> 00:07:42,540
Cheers!

83
00:07:48,890 --> 00:07:52,260
I seriously have to give it to you.

84
00:07:52,260 --> 00:07:54,410
Not everyone can put themselves second,

85
00:07:54,410 --> 00:07:59,420
and send their sister to college
after their parents passed.

86
00:07:59,420 --> 00:08:04,030
To think a crybaby like her
is now going to become a mother.

87
00:08:04,790 --> 00:08:07,920
You won't have to look after Rin anymore.

88
00:08:07,920 --> 00:08:10,460
So, you'd better start focusing on yourself.

89
00:08:10,460 --> 00:08:11,740
Erika...

90
00:08:11,740 --> 00:08:13,330
So, what's the plan now?

91
00:08:13,330 --> 00:08:17,050
You're quitting the job,
and letting your sister have the house.

92
00:08:17,050 --> 00:08:19,510
Yeah. Rin's family will only grow,

93
00:08:19,510 --> 00:08:23,770
so a single house is far too much for me.

94
00:08:23,770 --> 00:08:28,260
And I'll find a new job,
as long as I'm not choosy.

95
00:08:28,260 --> 00:08:30,810
Want me to introduce you
to my father's company?

96
00:08:30,810 --> 00:08:33,510
It's a similar sort of real estate job,

97
00:08:33,510 --> 00:08:36,720
and they have employee housing, too.

98
00:08:36,720 --> 00:08:40,920
Thanks, but I assume positions
will be scarce anyway.

99
00:08:40,920 --> 00:08:43,660
I suppose you're right.

100
00:08:43,660 --> 00:08:48,820
Maybe this was for the better.

101
00:08:48,820 --> 00:08:50,510
What do you mean?

102
00:08:51,400 --> 00:08:56,440
Finding out about my infertility
after marriage would've been worse.

103
00:08:56,440 --> 00:08:58,670
So, in a way,

104
00:08:58,670 --> 00:09:02,850
I think his rejection was in good faith.

105
00:09:03,720 --> 00:09:05,120
It was not.

106
00:09:05,120 --> 00:09:06,980
Himukai's a scumbag.

107
00:09:06,980 --> 00:09:09,290
Don't listen to that bastard.

108
00:09:09,290 --> 00:09:11,220
You dummy. Goody-two-shoes.

109
00:09:11,220 --> 00:09:14,110
- Erika, that's enough about him.
- Oh, I'm not done.

110
00:09:14,110 --> 00:09:16,070
He's pathetic. A momma's boy.

111
00:09:16,070 --> 00:09:17,520
A rich guy with no spine.

112
00:09:17,520 --> 00:09:19,320
I promise, I'm fine now.

113
00:09:19,320 --> 00:09:21,720
- There you go again.
- Huh?

114
00:09:21,720 --> 00:09:24,060
It's a bad habit of yours.

115
00:09:24,060 --> 00:09:28,290
You tend to hold back on yourself.

116
00:09:28,290 --> 00:09:32,040
You're allowed to complain
and rely on others, okay?

117
00:09:32,040 --> 00:09:36,080
Your friends and loved ones
will always be happy to listen.

118
00:09:38,560 --> 00:09:43,010
Then could I say just one thing?

119
00:09:43,010 --> 00:09:45,080
Lay it on me.

120
00:09:45,080 --> 00:09:47,280
When my marriage was called off,

121
00:09:47,280 --> 00:09:51,750
rumors about my body circulated the office.

122
00:09:51,750 --> 00:09:54,010
- What?
- That's one thing.

123
00:09:54,010 --> 00:09:56,340
That was a shocker in it of itself.

124
00:09:56,340 --> 00:10:00,610
But then, a junior of mine said...

125
00:10:00,610 --> 00:10:05,390
<i>They're practically saying
you've failed as a woman.</i>

126
00:10:05,390 --> 00:10:08,210
<i>Unforgivable.</i>

127
00:10:08,960 --> 00:10:14,720
Those words really shook me.

128
00:10:14,720 --> 00:10:17,200
Who the hell said that about you?

129
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:20,870
- I won't forgive her.
- No, I swear she's a nice girl.

130
00:10:20,870 --> 00:10:22,820
She just happened to make a biting remark.

131
00:10:22,820 --> 00:10:26,260
Still, that's nothing to say to...

132
00:10:26,260 --> 00:10:27,910
Hold on.

133
00:10:28,980 --> 00:10:30,620
[Misaki Takizawa]

134
00:10:30,620 --> 00:10:32,780
[How does this restaurant sound?]

135
00:10:34,610 --> 00:10:36,330
What's up?

136
00:10:38,430 --> 00:10:41,110
My department's holding

137
00:10:41,110 --> 00:10:44,940
a farewell party for me next Friday.

138
00:10:46,720 --> 00:10:49,810
[Palace of Versailles]

139
00:10:53,700 --> 00:10:55,610
Do you have any more?

140
00:10:57,610 --> 00:11:02,260
I'm so glad we could have dinner

141
00:11:02,260 --> 00:11:05,560
at one of your favorite restaurants, Sui.

142
00:11:05,560 --> 00:11:10,000
I've never been somewhere so fancy.
You've got great taste.

143
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:13,060
Great restaurant choice, Takizawa.

144
00:11:13,060 --> 00:11:15,200
Thank you.

145
00:11:15,200 --> 00:11:19,610
I wanted Sui to have one last
great memory with us here.

146
00:11:21,250 --> 00:11:23,350
What dish would you recommend?

147
00:11:23,350 --> 00:11:24,780
Huh?

148
00:11:25,480 --> 00:11:27,010
<i>The tripe's great here.</i>

149
00:11:27,010 --> 00:11:29,450
It's one of their specialties.

150
00:11:29,450 --> 00:11:32,520
"Tripe"? I've never had it before.

151
00:11:32,520 --> 00:11:33,620
You haven't?

152
00:11:33,620 --> 00:11:36,010
Score! A first for me!

153
00:11:36,010 --> 00:11:39,490
Then tripe will be a memorable dish for us.

154
00:11:39,490 --> 00:11:41,050
Yeah.

155
00:11:47,150 --> 00:11:51,490
Looks like this place specializes in tripe.

156
00:11:51,490 --> 00:11:54,760
Let's definitely order some of that.

157
00:11:58,210 --> 00:12:00,690
I'd recommend their other dishes as well.

158
00:12:01,930 --> 00:12:03,620
Like what?

159
00:12:03,620 --> 00:12:06,870
The escargot, and potatoes are great, too.

160
00:12:07,520 --> 00:12:09,130
- Everyone have a glass?
- Yes, sir.

161
00:12:09,130 --> 00:12:13,280
Here's to Monou's bright future. Cheers!

162
00:12:13,280 --> 00:12:15,840
Cheers!

163
00:12:15,840 --> 00:12:18,170
Thank you.

164
00:12:20,180 --> 00:12:22,070
That's good.

165
00:12:22,910 --> 00:12:25,570
Have you already found another job?

166
00:12:25,570 --> 00:12:27,600
Not yet.

167
00:12:27,600 --> 00:12:33,320
I'm sure you'll find a place
to utilize your CAD skills.

168
00:12:33,320 --> 00:12:34,560
Thanks.

169
00:12:34,560 --> 00:12:38,110
I did always love looking at architecture.

170
00:12:38,110 --> 00:12:41,740
Is there anything else
you've dreamt of doing?

171
00:12:41,740 --> 00:12:42,830
Not really.

172
00:12:42,830 --> 00:12:45,100
Taking it easy isn't so bad either.

173
00:12:45,100 --> 00:12:47,940
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

174
00:12:47,940 --> 00:12:50,730
Do you have any dreams yourself, Nakano?

175
00:12:50,730 --> 00:12:54,200
I'm too busy dealing with my newborn kid.

176
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:57,730
Can you believe my wife wants two more?

177
00:12:57,730 --> 00:13:00,950
- Kids are cute, so I understand.
- I suppose.

178
00:13:03,680 --> 00:13:06,610
Though kids aren't a necessity, of course.

179
00:13:06,610 --> 00:13:08,410
Right.

180
00:13:09,180 --> 00:13:10,660
Exactly!

181
00:13:10,660 --> 00:13:14,650
No kids, no marriage,
it's all up to the individual!

182
00:13:14,650 --> 00:13:17,330
Great point.

183
00:13:18,690 --> 00:13:21,630
Your glass is looking empty there, Sui.

184
00:13:21,630 --> 00:13:24,290
Sorry I didn't notice.

185
00:13:24,290 --> 00:13:28,130
Yes, drink up, Monou. It's your party.

186
00:13:29,240 --> 00:13:32,230
Don't be shy, eat your fill!

187
00:13:34,310 --> 00:13:35,890
How's that?

188
00:13:35,890 --> 00:13:37,190
Tastes great.

189
00:13:37,190 --> 00:13:40,360
Really?

190
00:13:40,360 --> 00:13:42,310
Thank you for all your hard work.

191
00:13:42,310 --> 00:13:45,030
- No, thank you.
- Take care.

192
00:13:45,030 --> 00:13:46,960
You sure you're not joining for round two?

193
00:13:46,960 --> 00:13:48,310
Yes.

194
00:13:48,310 --> 00:13:51,000
What a shame.

195
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:54,530
Keep in touch, okay?

196
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:57,760
Then let's mosey on to the next bar.

197
00:13:57,760 --> 00:13:59,370
- All right.
- See you, Monou.

198
00:13:59,370 --> 00:14:02,050
- Good night.
- Good luck.

199
00:14:02,050 --> 00:14:04,390
Get home safe.

200
00:14:04,390 --> 00:14:05,900
All right guys, drinks are on me!

201
00:14:05,900 --> 00:14:09,100
Yes!

202
00:14:25,890 --> 00:14:27,210
How about a drink on me?

203
00:14:27,210 --> 00:14:31,010
- No thank you.
- Aw, but you look free.

204
00:14:40,210 --> 00:14:42,730
Did you need something from my girlfriend?

205
00:14:44,810 --> 00:14:49,150
So, the uggo's got a boyfriend.

206
00:14:53,240 --> 00:14:55,220
Are you allright?

207
00:14:55,220 --> 00:14:58,360
Yes, thank you.

208
00:14:58,360 --> 00:15:00,880
You're drunk stupid.

209
00:15:02,280 --> 00:15:04,140
Where do you live?

210
00:15:05,640 --> 00:15:09,730
I don't wanna go home.

211
00:15:30,420 --> 00:15:33,060
Here, water. Drink up.

212
00:15:43,870 --> 00:15:45,660
Wait.

213
00:15:52,130 --> 00:15:53,790
Why?

214
00:15:56,050 --> 00:15:58,140
We're not doing anything?

215
00:16:09,850 --> 00:16:12,530
Don't try something you're not used to.

216
00:16:15,110 --> 00:16:16,700
<i>Sui is infertile?</i>

217
00:16:16,700 --> 00:16:18,740
<i>They're practically saying</i>

218
00:16:18,740 --> 00:16:22,390
<i>you've failed as a woman.</i>

219
00:16:32,510 --> 00:16:34,460
Don't go.

220
00:17:04,100 --> 00:17:08,190
<i>I don't care what happens anymore.</i>

221
00:17:22,390 --> 00:17:24,350
Please.

222
00:17:55,670 --> 00:17:58,880
I know this won't sound convincing, but...

223
00:18:04,300 --> 00:18:07,200
You ought to be more wary. You're a woman.

224
00:18:09,400 --> 00:18:11,270
A woman...

225
00:18:18,430 --> 00:18:20,850
Don't bother putting one on.

226
00:18:20,850 --> 00:18:22,520
You won't need to.

227
00:18:23,860 --> 00:18:27,700
I'll be fine.

228
00:18:27,700 --> 00:18:29,360
So...

229
00:18:43,920 --> 00:18:45,870
What are you talking about?

230
00:18:49,040 --> 00:18:52,280
These are for protecting your body.

231
00:19:45,100 --> 00:19:46,710
Morning.

232
00:19:49,720 --> 00:19:54,000
I'm so sorry. I was out of it yesterday.

233
00:20:03,300 --> 00:20:05,240
Feeling better?

234
00:20:06,000 --> 00:20:07,930
Yup.

235
00:20:07,930 --> 00:20:09,570
Thank you.

236
00:20:09,570 --> 00:20:11,670
That's all for us.

237
00:20:11,670 --> 00:20:14,020
Good bye.

238
00:20:30,890 --> 00:20:33,260
It's fine.

239
00:20:33,260 --> 00:20:36,090
I'll stay until you sleep.

240
00:21:07,800 --> 00:21:12,270
<i>Hey! How was the party yesterday?</i>

241
00:21:12,270 --> 00:21:13,950
It was complicated.

242
00:21:13,950 --> 00:21:17,570
But it gave me the motivation to move on.

243
00:21:17,570 --> 00:21:19,290
<i>As you should.</i>

244
00:21:19,290 --> 00:21:20,940
So, here's the thing.

245
00:21:29,440 --> 00:21:34,200
Could you introduce me to that job after all?

246
00:21:34,200 --> 00:21:36,870
The one at your father's workplace.

247
00:21:37,640 --> 00:21:39,690
Yeah, I want to give it a shot.

248
00:21:40,860 --> 00:21:42,680
Thanks.

249
00:21:42,680 --> 00:21:46,850
What, really?

250
00:21:46,850 --> 00:21:48,310
[Monou]

251
00:21:48,310 --> 00:21:51,040
So, the new hire is coming in next week?

252
00:21:51,040 --> 00:21:53,580
Yup. It seems she's an old friend of Erika's.

253
00:21:53,580 --> 00:21:56,370
Hopefully your spartan work ethic
won't scare her off.

254
00:21:56,370 --> 00:21:58,730
Hey!

255
00:21:58,730 --> 00:22:00,420
Although, I am a bit worried...

256
00:22:00,420 --> 00:22:03,830
Don't be, she'll warm up to you.

257
00:22:03,830 --> 00:22:06,030
That doesn't sound reassuring.

258
00:22:07,310 --> 00:22:08,390
How do you read her name?

259
00:22:08,390 --> 00:22:10,470
It's read, "Monou".

260
00:22:10,470 --> 00:22:12,870
"Monou".

261
00:22:12,870 --> 00:22:14,460
Unusual name, isn't it?

262
00:22:14,460 --> 00:22:16,400
- You could read it?
- Not at first.

263
00:22:16,400 --> 00:22:17,930
Glad I wasn't alone.

264
00:22:22,260 --> 00:22:26,220
I didn't think you'd move out so quick.

265
00:22:26,220 --> 00:22:30,860
Erika says I'm better off not dawdling.

266
00:22:30,860 --> 00:22:34,510
I'll miss having you around.

267
00:22:34,510 --> 00:22:37,670
But that's just me being selfish.

268
00:22:37,670 --> 00:22:40,530
Don't worry, I'll come back to help often.

269
00:22:40,530 --> 00:22:42,420
Thanks.

270
00:22:43,110 --> 00:22:48,500
Still, I can't help but worry
about a lady living alone...

271
00:22:48,500 --> 00:22:50,100
I'll be fine.

272
